HEADWORD: Soricine
<hw>So"ri*cine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sorricinus</ets>, fr. <ets>sorex</ets> a shrew.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the Shrew family
(<fam>Soricidae</fam>); like a shrew in form or habits; <as>as, the
<ex>soricine</ex> bat (<spn>Glossophaga soricina</spn>)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

